<DOC><DOCNO> AP880414-0125 </DOCNO><FILEID>AP-NR-04-14-88 1350EDT</FILEID><FIRST>r a PM-People-Vincent 1stLd-Writethru a0640 04-14 0193</FIRST><SECOND>PM-People-Vincent, 1st Ld-Writethru, a0640,0198</SECOND><HEAD>Actor Jan-Michael Vincent Arrested For Investigation of DrugPossession</HEAD><NOTE>Eds: Updates throughout with new info</NOTE><DATELINE>AGOURA HILLS, Calif. (AP) </DATELINE><TEXT>   Actor Jan-Michael Vincent wasarrested for investigation of felony drug possession after deputiesstopped his wife's car because its registration had expired andallegedly found amphetamines, authorities said today.   ``He was arrested for possession of 15 white amphetaminetablets'' Wednesday night, said Deputy Gabe Ramirez, a Los AngelesCounty sheriff's spokesman.   ``He was booked at Malibu (sheriff's) station,'' Ramirez said.``His arrest occurred after a car stop on Thousand Oaks Boulevardin Agoura Hills.''   Vincent, 42, was released after posting $1,000 bail, the deputysaid.   ``His wife was driving and he was a passenger,'' but his wifewasn't arrested, said Lt. John Love, of the sheriff's station inMalibu.   Love declined to specify how the drugs were discovered, but saidthe Vincents' car was stopped because it had an expired, 1986registration.   Vincent was cooperative during the arrest and booking, Love said.   Ramirez said the vehicle wasn't impounded, he said.   Agoura Hills is located about 30 miles northwest of downtown LosAngeles. Vincent lives nearby in Malibu.</TEXT></DOC>